                src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/GettyImages-2162572502_preview_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_embedColorProfile_true_quality_95.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=526&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=aa9b15c3f2d4e60801a1799032d9c456"
        srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/GettyImages-2162572502_preview_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_embedColorProfile_true_quality_95.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=263&amp;q=75&amp;w=400&amp;s=8046b7f06b9214fed30bc1c3ff58c669 400w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/GettyImages-2162572502_preview_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_embedColorProfile_true_quality_95.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=526&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=aa9b15c3f2d4e60801a1799032d9c456 800w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/GettyImages-2162572502_preview_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_embedColorProfile_true_quality_95.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=790&amp;q=75&amp;w=1200&amp;s=abe09cfd40d12ffe74ba1197f1c234ff 1200w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/GettyImages-2162572502_preview_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_embedColorProfile_true_quality_95.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=855&amp;q=75&amp;w=1300&amp;s=6e35fa56eb01d8f2a6919e3e9e5c633a 1300w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/GettyImages-2162572502_preview_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_embedColorProfile_true_quality_95.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=954&amp;q=75&amp;w=1450&amp;s=bc114fdb18ea3d8698ac186c70389e4f 1450w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/GettyImages-2162572502_preview_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_embedColorProfile_true_quality_95.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1053&amp;q=75&amp;w=1600&amp;s=fd8c783c0a5f71d4aae3183bee46169b 1600w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/GettyImages-2162572502_preview_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_embedColorProfile_true_quality_95.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=1316&amp;q=75&amp;w=2000&amp;s=7216cff0d2af5a6e58722ec98ccdce05 2000w"
                fetchpriority="high"    />


            
            
<figcaption class="attribution">
        <span class="attribution__caption">An evidence technician inventories a Glock 9 mm at a Chicago police firearms laboratory.</span>
    
        <span class="attribution__credit">
        <span class="a11y">Credit: </span>
        E. Jason Wambsgans/Chicago Tribune/Tribune News Service via Getty Images
    </span>
    
    
    </figcaption>

        </figure>
            <div class="opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper ">

                    <span class="opener__topics ">
            <a class="opener__topics-link " href="https://www.propublica.org/topics/regulation">Regulation</a>
        </span>
    
    <h1 class="opener__hed " >        Federal Law Thwarted Chicago’s Attempt to Sue Gun Makers. But Now It Has a New Strategy.
    </h1>

    <h2 class="opener__dek "  >        Taking advantage of a new state law, Chicago&#039;s lawsuit accuses Glock of manufacturing pistols with designs that allow modification and failing to make changes that would protect the public.
    </h2>
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

</div>
        
<div class="article-meta-1
     article-meta-1--left     " data-pp-location="article meta">

    <span class="article-meta-1__byline" data-pp-location="article byine">
        by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/vernal-coleman">Vernal Coleman</a>    </span>
    <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
        <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-07-30EDT05:00">July 30, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
    </time>

    <div class="article-meta-1__section-actions
            " data-pp-location="article story-tools">
